  <bioghist id="aspace_ffc2342b2a6406c2d6be4b32e009e3a9">
    <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
<p>Roland Politi is an Italian-born anarchist and artist who was involved in the 1980s squatters' rights movement in New York City's East Village which culminated in Tompkins Square Park Police Riot of August 1988.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_4936bff4dd9c9d9eddfecd77ab166d01">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>The collection contains newspaper clippings, subject files, including eviction notices, documents relating to the New York City Community Board, and commemorative t-shirts.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <userestrict id="aspace_24ff9f0a4747df6e964b3025f43fc241">
    <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
<p>Copyright (and related rights to publicity and privacy) to materials in this collection created by Roland Politi was not transferred to New York University. Permission to use materials must be secured from the copyright holder.</p>  </userestrict>
